SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: UNDER U.S. GAAP, AN ORGANIZATION MUST RECOGNIZE THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT EFFECTS OF A TAX POSITION TAKEN FOR TAX RETURN PURPOSES WHEN IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE POSITION WILL NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION. THE CORPORATION DOES NOT BELIEVE IT HAS TAKEN ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AND, ACCORDINGLY, IT HAS NOT RECORDED ANY LIABILITY FOR UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS. THE CORPORATION HAS FILED FOR AND RECEIVED INCOME TAX EXEMPTIONS IN THE JURISDICTIONS WHERE IT IS REQUIRED TO DO SO. THE CORPORATION IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDIT BY A TAXING AUTHORITY. AS OF JUNE 30, 2022 AND 2021, THE CORPORATION WAS NOT SUBJECT TO ANY EXAMINATION BY A TAXING AUTHORITY.

COMMUNITY ACCESS, INC., AN AFFILIATE OF THE REPORTING ORGANIZATION, PAID COMPENSATION TO THE REPORTING ORGANIZATION'S TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL. COMMUNITY ACCESS, INC. HAS ESTABLISHED THE COMPENSATION OF THE TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL USING FORM 990 OF OTHER ORGANIZATIONS, COMPENSATION SURVEY OR STUDY AND APPROVAL BY THE BOARD OR COMPENSATION COMMITTEE.
